My son wanted a travis Scott meal...which is a quarter pounder with cheese, fries, and a drink. I googled "how much is a Travis Scott meal", and McDonalds website said $6. I thought...ok....kevin likes this Travis scott fella, and its actually pretty cheap. $12 to feed the boys dinner and not have to do anything? Ok cool. So i called my mother in law, asked her if she wanted one...she said sure. So I get to mcdonalds, and they have removed all the prices off their menu...nothing has a price on it anymore. So I ask the lady, what's the difference between a Travis Scott meal and a quarter pounder meal? She says "nothing, except the Travis Scott meal has lettuce and bacon." I'm thinking great, that's awesome! Guess what? Travis Scott meals are $10 a piece!!! I get to the window and ask how much a quarter pounder meal costs....freaking $5.79. I asked why i saw the meal for $6 on their website...and apparently you HAVE to order it through the app in order to get it for $6. Im done with mcdonalds. Never going there again. I dont care if its the only place open and im starving to death. $3 just to add bacon and lettuce??? False advertising on the website? Ya...im totally done
